{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0a16622b-4b5b-4ea2-b028-d7225e781b48","content":"No existing files found in the workspace. Since this is a guidance request rather than an edit to existing code, here's how to convert your page:\n\n## 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"20\">\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font size: {0}'}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element. This tells the XAML compiler the type of `BindingContext`, so all `{Binding ...}` expressions are validated **at compile time**.\n\n## 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the compiler resolves property names and types. A typo like `{Binding Themee}` will now produce a **build error** instead of silently failing at runtime.\n\n## 3. Opting out locally\n\nIf a section binds to a different type (e.g. inside a `DataTemplate`), scope `x:DataType` there or opt out:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Different type in a template -->\n<CollectionView.ItemTemplate>\n    <DataTemplate x:DataType=\"vm:SettingItem\">\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Name}\" />\n    </DataTemplate>\n</CollectionView.ItemTemplate>\n\n<!-- Opt out for a dynamic binding -->\n<Label Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamic, x:DataType=x:Null}\" />\n```\n\nThat's it — `x:DataType` enables compiled bindings, and `MauiStrictXamlCompilation` ensures mismatches break the build.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9722dea1-88e5-47a4-8fe1-f80b148e047c","outputTokens":589},"id":"7319102a-e068-441d-a668-0b9a00fac5c5","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:58:53.282Z","parentId":"66422bf9-b3aa-45ba-89c0-25833eb84105"}
